CFGBVS-7#1 Warning
CONFIG_VOLTAGE with Config Bank VCCO  
The CONFIG_MODE property of current_design specifies a configuration mode (SPIx1) that uses pins in bank 14.  I/O standards used in this bank have a voltage requirement of 2.50.  However, the CONFIG_VOLTAGE for current_design is set to 3.3. If you're using any config pins in this bank, ensure that your configuration voltage is compatible with the I/O standards in banks used by your configuration mode.  Refer to device configuration user guide for more information.    Pins used by config mode: D18 (IO_L1P_T0_D00_MOSI_14), D19 (IO_L1N_T0_D01_DIN_14), E18 (IO_L3P_T0_DQS_PUDC_B_14), K19 (IO_L6P_T0_FCS_B_14), and V19 (IO_L15N_T2_DQS_DOUT_CSO_B_14)
Related violations: <none>

